description: In information security and information programming, a buffer overflow vulnerability is  an anomaly where a program writes data to a  buffer that overwrites the boundary of the buffer  and adjacent memory locations. Over the past  few years, buffer overflows vulnerability have  become the most common form of security risk.
stack based buffer overflow in MsIo64.sys, Proof of Concept Local Privilege Escalation to nt authority/system
keywords: escalation of privileges proof of concept
Windows escalation of privileges proof of concept
